No more misleading than the original poster's.

The orignal poster said that a 486 "doesn't have nearly the raw
processing power" of a SPARC 10.  I'd rate this statement as very
misleading.  Most SPARC 10's out there are single CPU's.  They may
be on the order of twice as fast as an average 486, but there exist
486's which are faster than a significant number of 10's.  That was
the statement I made.

