From: dubois@primate.wisc.edu (Paul DuBois)
Subject: Re: Imake doesn't like me :(
Date: 19 Nov 1993 12:27:16 -0600
Reply-To: dubois@primate.wisc.edu

From article <1993Nov18.112510.1@ulkyvx.louisville.edu>, by wdmays01@ulkyvx.louisville.edu:
>On to my next problem, When I get olvmn or vlfm or any X program that is
>source when I go to X and enter either or the following:

>xmkmf
>make

>or

>imake

>it dies and says ::3::Imake.tmpl not found, when I create this file it
>runs but gives no error but doesn't do anything. I have'nt seen any thing
>in the FAQs nor do I have a man page on the suject. Any and all help would
>be appreciated.

As a command, "imake" by itself will do nothing correctly without arguments.
xmkmf's supposed to supply arguments telling imake where to find the
configuration files.  You can take a look through it to find where it
passes the -I argument to imake.  If the directory named in that argument
isn't where your config files really are, imake won't be able to find the
template file Imake.tmpl and it won't build your Makefile.

Creating an empty Imake.tmpl won't do any good.  You need the real X
config files.  You can get more information from ftp.primate.wisc.edu
in /pub/imake-stuff and /pub/imake-book.
-- 
Paul DuBois
dubois@primate.wisc.edu

